<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5698&amp;p=51949#p51949"><![CDATA[
It's 512 bytes of code preloaded at $7000 (in cartridge RAM) before the game starts. The code is used to emulate mappers via software, thus all ROMs using them are hacked.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Mon Nov 02, 2009 8:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
